The dependency that you are using, adds a transitive runtime dependency of `software.amazon.awssdk:apache-client` (which has the `ApacheHttpClient` class in it) to the project. That&#39;s why you can see the `ApacheHttpClient` class in the search results. However, since this is only a runtime dependency, you can&#39;t use the `ApacheHttpClient` class in the code. To use `ApacheHttpClient` in the code, you need the compile time dependency of `software.amazon.awssdk:apache-client`. For that, you can add the below dependency with the version of your desire.

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
   &lt;groupId&gt;software.amazon.awssdk&lt;/groupId&gt;
   &lt;artifactId&gt;apache-client&lt;/artifactId&gt;
   &lt;version&gt;2.20.56&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

You can refer this for more details -
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sdk-for-java/latest/developer-guide/http-configuration-apache.html

